dcterms:description: The diabetes dataset comes from the Guangâ€™anmen Hospital, China Academy of Chinese Medical Sciences, Beijing. It has been analyzed for significant herb interactions discovery and symptom-herb patterns, exploring the relationship among symptoms and herbs, to support clinical decision-making process. In the dataset, there are 1915 outpatient records consisting of four parts: symptoms, syndromes, herbal prescriptions and outcomes which are annotated as effective or ineffective of herbal treatments by TCM clinical doctors based on the changes of blood glucose and hemoglobin levels.

dcterms:description: This dataset focuses on mining symptom-herb patterns from patient records using a tripartite graph approach, which helps in understanding the relationships between symptoms and herbs in the context of Traditional Chinese Medicine.
